  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Play Random\r\n\r\nYou can use `play random` to play similar tracks and add variety to your song. Let's apply that to the vocals from Tinashe's Gravity:\r\n\r\n1) Drag a <code style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 148, 202); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play random</code> block inside the empty repeat block already in the workspace [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=flyout-id:play_random_toolbox---id-up-inside:play_together_workspace)\r\n2) Drag out 3 <code style=\"background-color: rgb(116, 53, 178); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play</code> blocks and update them to be three different vocal Ad-Libs [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=flyout-id:play_toolbox)\r\n\r\nPress the <code style=\"background-color: #fca401; color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px1 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">Run</code> button! You should hear different vocals each time you press run!",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
